  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Hanuman Chalisa?",
  "response": "The Hanuman Chalisa is a devotional hymn dedicated to Lord Hanuman, a revered figure in Hinduism known for his unwavering devotion to Lord Rama, immense strength, and various heroic deeds. The word \"Chalisa\" comes from the Hindi term \"ch\u0101l\u012bs,\" which means forty, referring to the forty verses that make up the hymn.\n\nComposed by the poet-saint Tulsidas in the 16th century, the Hanuman Chalisa is written in Awadhi, a dialect of Hindi. Each verse praises Hanuman's virtues, recounts his exploits, and seeks his blessings, protection, and guidance.\n\nDevotees often recite the Hanuman Chalisa to invoke Hanuman's divine intervention in overcoming obstacles, gaining strength and courage, and seeking spiritual upliftment. It is believed that regular recitation of the Hanuman Chalisa can bring peace, prosperity, and protection from negative influences.",
